---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Header from '../../components/Header.astro';
import FloatingActionButton from '../../components/FloatingActionButton.astro';
import BlogContactCTA from '../../components/BlogContactCTA.astro';

const blogPost = {
    title: "Build Better Leadership with the G.U.E.S.S. Framework",
    date: "April 23, 2025",
    author: "Jonathon Broce"
};
---

<Layout title={`${blogPost.title} - Day 41 Thrive`}>
    <Header />
    <main class="blog-post">
        <article class="container">
            <header class="post-header">
                <h1>{blogPost.title}</h1>
                <div class="post-meta">
                    <span class="date">{blogPost.date}</span>
                    <span class="author">By {blogPost.author}</span>
                </div>
            </header>
            <div class="post-content">
                <h2>Introduction: Leadership Isn't a Title—It's a Skill Set</h2>
                <p>Some people think leadership is natural. You either have "it" or you don't. At Day 41 Thrive, we call bull on that.</p>
                
                <p>Leadership is built. It's trained. It's developed—just like muscles. And if you're willing to put in the reps, we've got the framework to help you grow.</p>
                
                <p>Introducing the G.U.E.S.S. Framework—our proven system for developing strong, resilient, and respected leaders in the contracting, construction, and service industries.</p>
                
                <p>Because when it comes to leadership, you shouldn't be guessing. You should be growing.</p>

                <h2>What Is the G.U.E.S.S. Framework?</h2>
                <p>The G.U.E.S.S. Framework is a step-by-step model to help leaders:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li>Unlock their potential</li>
                    <li>Empower their teams</li>
                    <li>Drive operational excellence</li>
                    <li>Lead with vision and humility</li>
                </ul>

                <p>Here's how it breaks down:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li>G — Grow: Develop yourself first</li>
                    <li>U — Unleash: Empower those around you</li>
                    <li>E — Enhance: Optimize how your team works</li>
                    <li>S — Strategize: Build a roadmap that works</li>
                    <li>S — Synchronize: Align your team around shared goals</li>
                </ul>

                <p>Let's walk through each pillar.</p>

                <h2>G — Grow: Leadership Starts with You</h2>
                <p>Before you can lead others, you have to lead yourself. Growth isn't optional—it's your responsibility.</p>

                <p>We use the S.E.E.D. Method:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li>🌱 Self-Reflect – Know your strengths, weaknesses, and blind spots</li>
                    <li>🌱 Expand – Stay curious, learn constantly, and seek outside input</li>
                    <li>🌱 Evolve – Don't cling to old habits; challenge yourself to adapt</li>
                    <li>🌱 Develop – Build daily habits that compound over time</li>
                </ul>

                <p>Great leaders are students first.</p>
                
                <p>If you're not growing, your team isn't either.</p>

                <h2>U — Unleash: Empower Others to Rise</h2>
                <p>Micromanagement kills culture. If your team can't move without your approval, you've built a bottleneck, not a business.</p>

                <p>We use the R.I.S.E. Model to unleash others:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li>🔥 Recognize potential in people—even before they see it themselves</li>
                    <li>🔥 Inspire through clear vision, purpose, and consistent encouragement</li>
                    <li>🔥 Support by removing obstacles and celebrating progress</li>
                    <li>🔥 Empower through autonomy, tools, and decision-making clarity</li>
                </ul>

                <p>When your team feels safe to try, fail, and grow, they thrive—and so does your business.</p>
                
                <p>Unleashed teams don't wait—they lead.</p>

                <h2>E — Enhance: Work Smarter, Not Just Harder</h2>
                <p>Your job as a leader is to constantly refine the way things get done.</p>

                <p>We use the F.L.O.W. Method to dial in operations:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li>⚙ Focus – Prioritize what matters most</li>
                    <li>⚙ Leverage – Use tools, tech, and delegation to your advantage</li>
                    <li>⚙ Optimize – Audit processes regularly and eliminate waste</li>
                    <li>⚙ Work Smart – Make space for deep work and clear thinking</li>
                </ul>

                <p>Enhancing your systems enhances your team.</p>
                
                <p>This isn't about making things "easier"—it's about making them more effective.</p>

                <h2>S — Strategize: Lead With a Playbook, Not a Panic Button</h2>
                <p>Too many leaders operate in reactive mode, fighting fires and guessing at growth. Real leaders plan with purpose.</p>

                <p>We use the S.M.A.R.T. Method:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li>📊 Specific – Goals should be clear and actionable</li>
                    <li>📊 Measurable – Track what matters, not just what's easy</li>
                    <li>📊 Achievable – Set targets that stretch but don't snap your team</li>
                    <li>📊 Relevant – Align with your company's true mission</li>
                    <li>📊 Time-Bound – Put real deadlines on big dreams</li>
                </ul>

                <p>Hope isn't a strategy. Set the plan, work the plan, adjust the plan.</p>

                <h2>S — Synchronize: Build Alignment That Moves Mountains</h2>
                <p>Even the best ideas fail if your team isn't rowing in the same direction.</p>

                <p>We use the T.E.A.M. Model to create alignment:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li>🤝 Trust – Build relationships that foster safety and respect</li>
                    <li>🤝 Engage – Keep people connected to the vision</li>
                    <li>🤝 Align – Make sure roles, goals, and values match</li>
                    <li>🤝 Mobilize – Give your team the tools, freedom, and fire to execute</li>
                </ul>

                <p>The best teams don't just execute—they believe.</p>
                
                <p>When your crew is synchronized, your business moves with power and purpose.</p>

                <h2>The Bottom Line: Stop Guessing. Start Leading.</h2>
                <p>Leadership isn't about being the loudest, the smartest, or the most experienced. It's about growing yourself, empowering others, and aligning your team to win—together.</p>

                <p>The G.U.E.S.S. Framework gives you the tools to do just that.</p>
                <ul>
                    <li>No fluff</li>
                    <li>No clichés</li>
                    <li>Just real frameworks, real reps, and real growth</li>
                </ul>

                <p>At Day 41 Thrive, we're here to help you build the kind of leadership your business—and your people—deserve.</p>

                <p>Let's stop guessing. Let's start thriving.</p>

                <p>You in?</p>

                <BlogContactCTA />
            </div>
        </article>
    </main>
    <FloatingActionButton />
</Layout>

<style>
    .blog-post {
        padding-top: 80px;
    }

    .container {
        max-width: 800px;
        margin: 0 auto;
        padding: 2rem 1rem;
    }

    .post-header {
        margin-bottom: 2rem;
        text-align: center;
    }

    h1 {
        color: var(--primary);
        font-size: clamp(2rem, 4vw, 3rem);
        margin-bottom: 1rem;
        line-height: 1.2;
    }

    .post-meta {
        display: flex;
        justify-content: center;
        gap: 1rem;
        color: var(--text);
        opacity: 0.8;
    }

    .post-content {
        color: var(--text);
        line-height: 1.8;
    }

    .post-content h2 {
        color: var(--primary);
        margin: 2rem 0 1rem;
        font-size: clamp(1.5rem, 3vw, 2rem);
    }

    .post-content p {
        margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
    }

    .post-content ul {
        margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
        padding-left: 1.5rem;
    }

    .post-content li {
        margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
    }

    .post-content strong {
        color: var(--primary);
    }

    @media (max-width: 768px) {
        .container {
            padding: 1.5rem;
        }
    }
</style>